    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. Let's address the technical issues directly:\n\n1. **Connection Timeout**: This could be due to network latency or resource contention. Consider implementing a retry mechanism with exponential backoff to handle transient failures. Additionally, review your database connection pool settings to ensure there are enough connections available during peak traffic.\n\n2. **Failed Lock Acquisition**: This indicates that the service is unable to acquire a lock on the database transaction. To resolve this, you can:\n   - Optimize the transaction scope to be as short as possible to reduce lock contention.\n   - Review the locking strategy and ensure that locks are held for the minimum time necessary.\n   - Implement a deadlock detection and resolution mechanism if not already in place.\n\n3. **Deadlock Detected**: Deadlocks occur when two or more transactions are waiting for each other to release locks. To prevent deadlocks:\n   - Analyze the transaction logs to identify the resources and order in which locks are being acquired.\n   - Enforce a consistent lock acquisition order across all transactions.\n   - Consider using optimistic concurrency control if applicable.\n\n4. **Internal Server Error**: This is a catch-all error that can be caused by various issues. To troubleshoot:\n   - Enable detailed error logging",
